<task id="022" project="spaarke-environment-provisioning-app">
  <metadata>
    <title>Add Per-Record Validation for Grid Approve</title>
    <phase>3</phase>
    <tags>client, ribbon, js</tags>
    <estimate>30m</estimate>
    <status>pending</status>
    <dependencies>020</dependencies>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    <goal>In the grid approveRequest function, check each selected record for environment lookup. Records without environment set should fail individually with message (FR-07).</goal>
    <context>FR-07: Per-record error: "{Name}: No target environment selected". Grid approve iterates selected records. Records with environment proceed; records without show error but don't block others.</context>
    <constraints>
      - Check sprk_dataverseenvironmentid on each record before calling API
      - Error message per record: "{Name}: No target environment selected"
      - Records with environment still get approved
      - Use Xrm.WebApi.retrieveRecord to get lookup value if not in grid columns
    </constraints>
  </prompt>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>src/client/webresources/js/sprk_registrationribbon.js</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-environment-provisioning-app/spec.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step>Read grid approveRequest function</step>
    <step>Before calling API for each record, check if environment lookup is set</step>
    <step>If not set: add to error list with "{Name}: No target environment selected"</step>
    <step>If set: proceed with approve API call</step>
    <step>After all records: show summary of errors if any</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool>Read</tool>
    <tool>Edit</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output>src/client/webresources/js/sprk_registrationribbon.js (modified)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>Records without environment fail individually</criterion>
    <criterion>Error message includes record name</criterion>
    <criterion>Records with environment still get approved</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
